column1: # This file is automatically generated by the grid engine. The file contains
# mappings for the parameters found from the content server
# mappings already defined. The point is that the query server cannot find
# requested parameters without mappings. On the other hand
# is also the search order of the parameters that do not contain complete search
# If you want to change some of the mappings or their order
# them to a permanent mapping file (which is not automatically overridden.
#            11 Level at specified pressure difference from ground to level
#            13 Layer between two metric heights above ground
#            14 Layer between two depths below land surface
#         bit 0 = Climatological parameter (=> ignore year when searching)
#         bit 1 = Global parameter (=> ignore timestamp when searching
# 13) Search match (Can this mapping used when searching mappings for incomplete parameters)
# 14) Mapping function (enables data conversions during the mapping)
